ENTRY            41557   20260112   20260319   20260319       4226
SUBENT        41557001   20260112   20260319   20260319       4226
BIB                  8         24
TITLE       Fragments yields in spontaneous fission and
           photofission of 248Cm
AUTHOR     (Yu.P.Gangrskii, V.I.Zhemenik, N.Yu.Maslova,
           G.V.Myshinskii, Yu.E.Penionzhkevich)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB) Yu.P.Gangrsii, N.Yu.Maslova, G.V.Myshinskii,
                     Yu.E.Penionzhkevich.
           (4UKRIJD)  V.I.Zhemenik.
REFERENCE  (J,PPN/L,2,92,2005) Engl.translation of FCY/L.
           (J,FCY/L,2,(2),44,2005) Main reference. Issue 2(125)
           (C,2004BELGOR,,80,2004) Prelim.data for Subent 002.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) HPGe-detector of 150 cm**3 volume, 2.1 keV
           resolution for 1133 keV gamma-line of Co-60.
SAMPLE     Oxide CmO2 layer of 15 mm diameter, 0.6 mg/cm**2
           thickness on Ti backing of 1.5 microm thickness.
           Number of Cm-248 nuclei 2.E+18.
REL-REF    (O,M0813001,Yu.P.Gangrskii,J,FCY/L,2,(2),44,2005)
           Data of Tables 1,2 for photo-fission.
HISTORY    (20110401C) M.M.
           (20141220U) Ref.of Engl.translation was added.
            Subents 002, 003 were corrected.
           (20200925U) Ref. C,2004BELGOR,,80,2004 was added.
           (20260112A) Subent 004 was moved in M0813 according to
            a comment of N.Otsuka (NDS, IAEA).
            STATUS was updated for new rules.
ENDBIB              24
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           27
SUBENT        41557002   20260112   20260319   20260319       4226
BIB                  7         21
REACTION   ((96-CM-248(0,F)ELEM/MASS,IND,FY)/
           (96-CM-248(0,F)54-XE-138,IND,FY))
           Xe isotopes yields relative to Xe-138 yield taken as
           100. Data were multiplied by 0.01 by compiler.
REL-REF    (M,,Yu.P.Gangrskiy+,J,PTE,,(3),67,2002)
            Details of method
           (R,12895001,G.P.Ford+,J,PR/C,30,(1),195,1984)
           Xe-135 isomeric ratio used in analysis to define Xe-135
           total yield (only isomeric state was observed).
METHOD     (GSPEC) Xe yields were defined from its gamma-spectra.
ANALYSIS          Gamma-lines areas were used to define fission
           yields.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Type of uncertainty is not explained in the
           article.
STATUS     (TABLE,,Yu.P.Gangrskii,J,PPN/L,2,92,2005) Table 2.
            Prelim.data in Table of Conf.Proc.2004BELGOR,p.80,2004
HISTORY    (20141229A) 96-CM-248(0,F)ELEM/MASS,IND,FY,,REL ->
            (96-CM-248(0,F)ELEM/MASS,IND,FY)/
            (96-CM-248(0,F)54-XE-138,IND,FY) according to the
             comment of N.Otsuka (NDS,IAEA).
           (20200925U) STATUS information was updated.
ENDBIB              21
